,"nameMeanings":[{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry FitzHervey of Ravensworth was born in 1167, in Ravensworth, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Hervey FitzAkaris de Ravensworth. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Alice Greystoke. He died on 16 March 1212, in his hometown, at the age of 45, and was buried in East Witton, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"1167–16 March 1212":"1167–16. märts 1212","1167–1212":"1167–1212","1169–Male":"1169–Surnud","1162–1213":"1162–1213","1190–1243":"1190–1243","1201–1219":"1201–1219","1203–1243":"1203–1243","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1130–1182":"1130–1182","1190":"1190","about 1182":"umbes 1182","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","1205":"1205","1203":"1203","16 March 1212":"16. märts 1212","Abt 1201":"umbes 1201","1213":"1213","1169":"1169","1201":"1201","1212":"1212","1167":"1167","1243":"1243","after 16 March 1212":"pärast 16. märtsi 1212","1219":"1219","Ravensworth, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ravensworth, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","East Witton, Yorkshire, England":"East Witton, Yorkshire, England","Jervaulx Abbey, Ripon, Yorkshire, England":"Ripon, Yorkshire, England","Ravensworth, Yorkshire, England":"Ravensworth, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1167–16 March 1212":"1167–16. maaliskuuta 1212","1167–1212":"1167–1212","1169–Male":"1169–Kuollut","1162–1213":"1162–1213","1190–1243":"1190–1243